SIMPLE: hurl
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hurl
<hw>Hurl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Hurled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hurling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>hurlen</ets>,
<ets>hourlen</ets>; prob. contracted fr. OE. <ets>hurtlen</ets> to
hurtle, or probably akin to E. <ets>whirl</ets>. ⟦root⟧16. See
<er>Hurtle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To send whirling or whizzing
through the air; to throw with violence; to drive with great force;
<as>as, to <ex>hurl</ex> a stone or lance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>hurl'd</qex> them headlong to their fleet and main.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To emit or utter with vehemence or impetuosity;
<as>as, to <ex>hurl</ex> charges or invective</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[Cf. <er>Whirl</er>.]</ety> <def>To twist or
turn.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Hurled</xex> or crooked feet.⟦rdquo⟧
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hurl
<hw>Hurl</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To hurl one's self; to
go quickly.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To perform the act of hurling something; to throw
something (at another).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God shall <qex>hurl</qex> at him and not spare.</q> <rj><qau>Job
xxvii. 22 (Rev. Ver. ).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To play the game of hurling. See
<er>Hurling</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hurl
<hw>Hurl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of hurling or
throwing with violence; a cast; a fling.</def>
<rj><au>Congreve.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tumult; riot; hurly-burly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Knolles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Hat Manuf.)</fld> <def>A table on which fiber is
stirred and mixed by beating with a bowspring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurlbat</ent>⟦br⟧
